# {{project-name}} — Developer Reference

Built with the Boundary Framework. Follows the Functional Core / Imperative Shell (FC/IS) pattern.

---

## Essential Commands

```bash
# REPL (nREPL on port 7888) — JWT_SECRET is pre-set in .env
source .env
clojure -M:repl-clj

# Shorthand via bb tasks
bb repl          # same as clojure -M:repl-clj
bb test          # same as clojure -M:test
bb migrate up    # same as clojure -M:migrate up

# In the REPL (dev/user.clj defines these aliases):
(go)    # start the system — http://localhost:3000
(reset) # reload changed namespaces and restart
(halt)  # stop the system

# Testing
clojure -M:test                   # all tests
clojure -M:test --focus-meta :unit        # unit tests only
clojure -M:test --focus-meta :integration # integration tests

# Database
clojure -M:migrate up    # run pending migrations

# Modules
boundary add <module>          # add an optional module
boundary list modules          # human-readable module list
boundary list modules --json   # machine-readable catalogue (for AI tools)

# Scaffolding — ALWAYS prefer this over hand-writing module code
bb scaffold ai "product module with name, price, stock" --yes   # natural language (needs AI provider)
bb scaffold generate --module-name product --entity Product \
  --field name:string:required --field price:decimal:required   # explicit, no AI needed
bb scaffold integrate product  # wire module into deps.edn / tests.edn / wiring
bb guide next                  # state-aware: what should happen next?

# AI tooling (needs Ollama or ANTHROPIC_API_KEY / OPENAI_API_KEY)
bb ai explain --file stacktrace.txt   # explain a Clojure/Boundary error
bb ai gen-tests src/path/to/ns.clj    # generate a test namespace
bb ai sql "find active users with orders in last 7 days"  # HoneySQL from NL
bb setup ai "PostgreSQL with Stripe payments"             # AI-powered config setup
bb doctor --all                       # validate config + environment
bb check                              # quality gates (FC/IS, deps, lint)
```

