## Architecture: Functional Core / Imperative Shell

```
src/{{project-ns}}/
├── core/    # Pure functions ONLY — business logic, calculations, transformations
│             # No I/O, no logging, no exceptions, no side effects
└── shell/   # All side effects — HTTP handlers, DB access, external calls, services
```

<!-- gen:fc-is -->
| Direction | Allowed? |
|-----------|----------|
| Shell → Core | ✅ allowed |
| Core → Ports | ✅ allowed |
| Shell → Ports | ✅ allowed |
| Core → Shell | ❌ NEVER — violates FC/IS |
| Core → IO | ❌ NEVER — even logging |

Every module MUST define `ports.clj`.

- core/ must not import shell/IO/logging/DB
- cross-module calls go through service ports
- web/HTTP layers never require *.shell.persistence directly

```clojure
(ns {{project-ns}}.core.product)
(defn calculate-total [items] (reduce + (map :price items)))
```
<!-- /gen:fc-is -->

```clojure
;; ✅ CORRECT — core is pure
(ns {{project-ns}}.core.product)
(defn calculate-total [items] (reduce + (map :price items)))

;; ❌ WRONG — core must never do I/O
(ns {{project-ns}}.core.product
  (:require [{{project-ns}}.shell.persistence :as db]))  ; NEVER
```

**Module structure when adding new functionality:**

```
src/{{project-ns}}/
├── schema.clj               # Malli validation schemas (shared)
├── ports.clj                # Protocol definitions (interfaces)
├── core/
│   └── {domain}.clj         # Pure business logic
└── shell/
    ├── persistence.clj      # Database access
    ├── service.clj          # Business operations (orchestrates core + adapters)
    └── http.clj             # HTTP handlers and routes
```

