## AI Agent Tooling

The agent decision table (scaffold, `bb ai explain|gen-tests|sql|docs`,
`bb setup ai`, `bb doctor`, `bb guide`) lives in
`.claude/skills/boundary/SKILL.md` — auto-discovered by Claude Code and
compatible agentic CLIs. Rule of thumb: **scaffold, don't hand-write.**

Install once with bbin to enable REPL-driven development from the terminal:

```bash
bbin install https://github.com/bhauman/clojure-mcp-light.git --tag v0.2.2 \
  --as clj-nrepl-eval --main-opts '["-m" "clojure-mcp-light.nrepl-eval"]'

bbin install https://github.com/bhauman/clojure-mcp-light.git --tag v0.2.2 \
  --as clj-paren-repair --main-opts '["-m" "clojure-mcp-light.paren-repair"]'
```

```bash
clj-nrepl-eval --discover-ports      # find running REPLs
clj-nrepl-eval -p 7888 "(+ 1 2)"     # evaluate an expression
clj-paren-repair src/my_ns/core.clj  # repair after edits
```

### MCP server

This project ships a wired Boundary MCP server (`.mcp.json`). Open Claude Code or
Cursor in the project root and the agent gains Boundary's tools (lint, scaffold,
run-tests, …) with no setup. The server is launched via the `:mcp` deps alias
(`clojure -M:mcp`) and is absent from the app runtime classpath, so it never ships
with your application.

